Doug Hughes, 61, is 'lucky to be alive' and 'should have been blown out of the air,' Rep . 
  Jason Chaffetz said . 
  Hughes piloted a small gyrocopter through protected Washington airspace to the Capitol . 
  He was tracked by the Secret Service and Capitol Police and landed on the West Lawn . 
  Hughes was charged with two federal crimes, violating restricted airspace and operating an unregistered aircraft . 
  Security officials feared harming tourists on the National Mall if they tried to shoot him down . 
  Hughes ' flew under the radar' for 30 miles before landing on the lawn . 
 